<br>
How many Level 16 meleer's do you see walking around with a Wurmslayer? Lots.<br>
<br>
Plain and simple. Put a cap on weapons like they do spells, and the game will be fun again for all casters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 540<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 11:05 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cap Weapons</span><hr size=1> Aye, thats been suggested awhile ago.  And I still support the notion.  Would it make it so my melee twink would have to get back to grass roots fighting?  Sure.  But the balancing effect would be GREAT.   They can obviously put a level restriction on the Effects attached to certain armor and weapons.  And they can place race and deity restrictions on jewelry in addition to armor and weapons.  There is NO reason they wouldn't be able to put the level restriction on the armor and weapons themselves. (i.e.  You are not yet powerful enough to wield this weapon -or- You are not yet powerful enough to wear this armor)  Simple.   Yeah, a TON of people would complain.  Fine, GET OVER IT!  If you've been here since the game started (like myself and many others), you had to start out with nothing ANYWAY. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith2.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 11:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cap Weapons</span><hr size=1> No one talks about twink wizards, heh.<br>
<br>
There is no way the engine would support this, but I'd like to see items that ramped with your level and/or with your faction with your diety.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>
59 wizard of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/01 7:59 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cap Weapons</span><hr size=1> Of course the engine would support it, why wouldn't it support it.  Just add a min level to all magic items, no matter the type.<br>
<br>
Casters can't memorize a spell above our level even if it's in our spellbook.  Melees shouldn't be able to use magic armor and weapons unless they are of the appropriate level.  <br>
<br>
Now, from a historical perspective, armor needed to be properly fit and sized in order to be fully effective.  If you were a bit bigger or smaller than who the armor was made for, it will either hinder movement, or rub the person who's wearing it to the point where they WILL be feeling pain.  Now, magic armor has the feature you don't need to resize it, the armor does that magically, BUT, there's no reason it should happen to someone who isn't worthy of wearing such a piece of magic armor.  The extra combat ability of a sword doesn't NEED to be effective for EVERYONE, the weapon's enchantment could be that it only works for those IT feels is worthy. There's a book, &quot;By the Sword&quot; by Mercedes Lackey that tells the story about an intelligent sword, but even when it was &quot;sleeping&quot;, it was only fully effective for it's magic properties when wielded by a woman.  That book is just one example of how &quot;level restrictions&quot; on weapons could and would make sense.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 56 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugarielhalliwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gariel Halliwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/01 8:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I heard there are level restriction</span><hr size=1> A warrior friend of mine said he got his Club of the Ice Ocean off a twink who didn't know you had to be level 50 to wield it, so, according to him, there are weapons out there with a level cap.<br>
