<br>
This would add a very nice aspect to the game so that a 60 level warrior who suddenly finds a nice one hand blut he'd like to use had better darn well hope he has his skill up to 250 to use it.  If he dosent he can go buy a crappy 1 hand blunt and practice tell the magical weapon finaly deams him worthy of letting him be its master.  In storys many magical weapons had minds of there own. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uardius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ardius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/01 12:35 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cap Weapons</span><hr size=1> I realize this isn't exactly what you're talking about... You want them to not be able to equip and/or use the wep at all, and personally, I agree, however that ain't ever going to happen on a large scale, but...<br>
<br>
As far as I know, there is a cap on melee weapons, known as the damage cap, and it's been there since day 1.  Under level 20, all melee weapons are capped at 10 damage (which is to say the max unmodified damage you can do in one swing is 21).  So that warrior twink who is walking around with a 25 damage Wurmslayer at level 16 is not getting any benefit from it, really, other than likely consistently hitting for 21s, and looking cool, for whatever that's worth.  In fact there are probably 1hs weps out there with a damage of 10 or so, and a delay considerably less than the 40 of the Wurmslayer, which would actually be more effective weapons for someone &lt; level 20 because of the greater speed.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 copper.<br>
<br>
Ard.<br>
